      • loadFromInternet

        public void loadFromInternet(ImageView imageView,
                    java.lang.Object URL,
                    boolean fitExactly,
                    AsyncLoader.Callback callback)
        Images will be downloaded from internet and desplayed on the ImageView.
        If fitExactly is true, then the image Width Height will be the same as the ImageView Width and Height. Ohterwise the image will decoded with respect to the Width and Height of the given ImageView.
        Both callback and imageview cannot be null.
        If no imageView is provided, then the default image will be pass to the callback.
        URL string cannot be null.
        If callback is provided, the image will be provided to the callback as a drawable.

        Important: If imageview is null, the image will not be optimized. which mean, you are only trying to get the image not to display it. for that, use the other loadFromInternet(..) method
        Parameters:
        imageView -
        URL -
        fitExactly -
        callback -
        See Also:
        loadFromInternet(ImageView imageView, Object URL, int width, int height, boolean fitExactly, Callback callback)
